<HL>
   Canadian Steel Production
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel production totaled 162,642 metric
tons in the week ended last Saturday, up 2.1% from 159,248
tons in the preceding week but down 42% from 278,888 tons a
year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said. A
metric ton is equal to about 2,204.62 pounds.
   For this year through last Saturday, production fell 16%
to 9.6 million metric tons from 11.4 million tons a year
earlier.
</LP>
