<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   All Dazzle, No Sale
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<CO>
   HMX
</CO>
<IN>
TEXTILES AND APPAREL (TEX)
</IN>
<LP>
   Regarding your Aug. 27 page-one article on Hartmarx and
men's clothing, I wonder how your writer could take such a
skewed approach. According to him, soon I shall be called
upon by men robed in mustard-colored, Italian-cut $1,000
suits. No doubt I'll be so disarmed and distracted that I'll
fail to concentrate on their salesmanship. Enter the dowdy
fellow in an American-made Hartmarx or Brooks Brothers -- the
poor guy; his appearance is so ordinary that he actually
closes the deal with me.
   Betsey Lynch
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Cincinnati
</TEXT>
