<HL>
   Who's News:
   Novatny Resigns Posts
   At Laclede Gas Co.
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LG WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
GAS UTILITIES (GAS)
</IN>
<LP>
   ST. LOUIS -- Laclede Gas Co. said that its president and
chief operating officer Donald A. Novatny, 55 years old,
resigned from the company, effective Monday, for personal
reasons.
   Succeeding Mr. Novatny in both positions at the natural
gas distributor is Robert C. Jaudes, 56, executive vice
president-operations and marketing.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lee Liberman, chairman and chief executive officer, said
in a written statement that Mr. Novatny's resignation was
unexpected.
   "I had intended to recommend his promotion to chief
executive officer of the company at our annual meeting next
January. However, he told me he had decided after much
thought that he simply did not want the responsibilities and
pressures" associated with that job, Mr. Liberman said.
   A Laclede spokesman said that Mr. Novatny was unavailable
to comment on his resignation.
</TEXT>
