<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Assets of the nation's 524 money-market
funds rose $361.6 million, to $409.12 billion, in the week
ended Wednesday, according to the Investment Company
Institute, a Washington-based trade association.
   Assets of 256 general-purpose funds rose $681.3 million,
to $145.53 billion, and assets of 105 broker-dealer funds
fell $505.5 million, to $165.1 billion. Assets of 163
institutional funds rose $185.8 million, to $98.48 billion.
