   Business Brief -- Degussa AG:
   ASTA Unit Buys Temmler,
   A Pharmaceutical Business
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   G.DGS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)
</IN>
<LP>
   Degussa AG, a West German chemical and metal concern, said
its ASTA Pharma AG unit bought a family-owned pharmaceutical
business, Temmler-Group G.m.b.H. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Temmler, which expects 1990 sales of 25 million marks
($15.9 million), makes medicines indicated for colds, asthma,
headaches, bronchitis and digestive disorders. With the
acquisition, Frankfurt-based ASTA said it expects to solidify
its national and global market strength by marketing an
additional line of products.
